cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new algorithm to improve the performance of deep reinforcement learning agents. The algorithm is evaluated on both a 2D MNIST Maze environment and 49 games of the Atari 2600 environment. Given the focus on deep reinforcement learning and the evaluation on Atari games, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
